cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper is about a socially aware peer-to-peer service that collects social information from multiple sources into a multigraph managed in a decentralized fashion on user-contributed nodes. It also discusses simulations and experiments on PlanetLab with emulated application workloads. Based on this, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DB (Databases), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
